Seems the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Watch_Foundation">Internet Watch Foundation</a> are at it again! Sub-domains of <a href="http://www.webs.com/">Webs.com</a> are currently inaccessible to anyone in the UK who's ISP pays attention to the IWF. This means that I am being blocked from visiting my own Web site ( http://chriswarbo.webs.com ) because it contains child porn (the only reason the IWF blocks sites). Hmm. <del>You can visit it via its old address  ( http://www.freewebs.com&nbsp;/&nbsp;chriswarbo ) and judge for yourself how much is illegal pornography, or you can visit it through <a href="http://proxy.org/cgi_proxies.shtml">a non-UK proxy</a>. Annoyingly the <a href="http://www.tk/">www.tk</a> servers won't let me change the redirect address of http://www.chriswarbo.tk . I think it may have expired :'(</del> If you think this is ridiculous then do what I do, support the <a href="http://www.openrightsgroup.org">Open Rights Group</a> :)
